  "findings": [
    "Each GB200 NVL72 rack is a fully liquid-cooled, rack-scale design containing 36 Grace CPUs, 72 Blackwell GPUs, up to 13.5 TB HBM3E, and a 130 TB/s NVLink domain.",
    "The GB200 NVL72 rack is equipped with six 1U 33 kW power shelves (three front, three rear), implying a total rack power draw on the order of ~100 kW per rack.",
    "Each GB200 NVL72 compute tray uses 4 × 400 Gb/s OSFP ConnectX-7 NICs and 2 × BlueField-3 DPUs for networking, and is compatible with an in-rack or in-row CDU for liquid cooling.",
    "The DGX SuperPOD for the Vera Rubin generation is built with eight DGX Vera Rubin NVL72 systems and is defined as the minimum unit at which AI factory economics, reliability, and performance converge in production environments.",
    "AI factories can draw hundreds of megawatts of power, and roughly 30% of power is lost to conversion, distribution, and cooling before reaching the GPUs, representing a key constraint on how much compute can be deployed per megawatt."
  ],
